        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 16 at 1:18AM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 118 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arroyo Hondo, or 9 miles south of Questa, moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Questa, Red River, Taos Ski Valley, Arroyo Seco, Amalia, Arroyo
Hondo, Costilla, Taos Pueblo, Cerro and Lama.

This includes Highway 64 between Mile Markers 237 and 238.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
